mediaNotes: Second reel-to-reel tape for this Barred Owl recording event.   In this recording the male and female give the Barred Owl's maniacal caterwaul.

Recording of Barred Owl made on Irish Hill Road at Arnot Forest.  Approximate coordinates for this recording are 42.286142, -76.657199.  The recording effort began at about dusk and continued until after darkness fell.   A pair of birds responded to vocal imitations by Charles R. Smith.  First response to imitations came from a considerable distance downslope.   Stimulated by repeated imitations from Smith, the birds continued to move upslope toward us to the relatively close distance heard in this recording.   Throughout the recording there are imitations by Smith.

location.name: 17064 South Schweiger Drive, Olathe, Kansas, US (38.819, -94.771)

mediaNotes: Both birds were singing, sometimes in close physical proximity, sometimes quite separated as they moved between the roadside and further back in the forest.  The last few songs were from a mid-storey perch at the roadside.  There was also singing in flight and caterwauling.  Fighter jet in the background (recorded near Cold Lake Air Weapons Range).

NOTES: 21 single "woo-ah" call notes given by one bird of a pair of birds present in low trees in the parking lot at Paurotis Pond in Everglads National Park.  All under natural conditions.  Note the soft four notes starting at 8:00.  Unsure if these soft calls were given by the same individual as was giving the main vocs in this cut.  Note that this is a different individual than that recorded at Mahogany Hammock (LNS 135413).
